The paper discusses the development of an effective policy for End User Computing (EUC) and the process of bringing critical EUC applications into a controlled environment. This involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR), software engineering (cs.SE), cybersecurity (cs.CY), programming languages (cs.PL), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
